  "text": "Caudal epididymal sperm resuspended in HB þ at a final concentration of 2 3 10 8 sperm/ml were sonicated on ice with an ultrasonic cell disruptor (QSonica) for three times at 10 sec each at 30% amplitude. The sonicate was centrifuged at 16 000 3 g for 20 min at 48C, and the supernatant was collected as the soluble fraction. The pellet (insoluble fraction) was resuspended in an equal volume of HB þ . The soluble and insoluble fractions of the sonicates were utilized for phosphatase enzyme activity measurement on the same day. Radiolabeled phosphorylase a was used as a substrate to measure the activity of PP1 by procedures previously reported [CITATION_1] . Aliquots of the fractions of sperm extracts were preincubated at 308C for 15 min in either the presence or absence of protein phosphatase inhibitors. Purified protein phosphatase inhibitor-2 (I-2) was used at a final concentration of 25 nM to inhibit PP1 or 2 nM okadaic acid final concentration to selectively inhibit PP2A. Phosphorylase a was then added and the samples were further incubated at 308C for 10 min. The reaction was terminated by addition of 10% trichloroacetic acid and centrifuged for 10 min at 12 000 3 g. Supernatants were quantitated for [CITATION_2] P released from phosphorylase a.",
